1494","1416–Male":"1416–Afdød","1314–Male":"1314–Afdød","1313–Female":"1313–Afdød","1395":"1395","1494":"1494","1390":"1390","Abt 1415":"omkring 1415","1415":"1415","1435":"1435","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1445":"1445","1398":"1398","1441":"1441","1485":"1485","1416":"1416","28 October 1445":"28. oktober 1445","Ottringtown, Cambridge, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Ashford, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Ashford, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1395–28 October 1445":"1395–28 oktober 1445","1395–1445":"1395–1445","1398–1441":"1398–1441","1390–1485":"1390–1485","1415–1494":"1415–1494","1416–Male":"1416–Overleden","1314–Male":"1314–Overleden","1313–Female":"1313–Overleden","1395":"1395","1494":"1494","1390":"1390","Abt 1415":"circa 1415","1415":"1415","1435":"1435","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1445":"1445","1398":"1398","1441":"1441","1485":"1485","1416":"1416","28 October 1445":"28 oktober 1445","Ottringtown, Cambridge, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Ashford, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Ashford, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Otterden, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England, United Kingdom":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1395–28 October 1445":"1395–28 October 1445","1395–1445":"1395–1445","1398–1441":"1398–1441","1390–1485":"1390–1485","1415–1494":"1415–1494","1416–Male":"1416–Deceased","1314–Male":"1314–Deceased","1313–Female":"1313–Deceased","1395":"1395","1494":"1494","1390":"1390","Abt 1415":"about 1415","1415":"1415","1435":"1435","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1445":"1445","1398":"1398","1441":"1441","1485":"1485","1416":"1416","28 October 1445":"28 October 1445","Ottringtown, Cambridge, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Ashford, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Ashford, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"St","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Southern French: variant of   St  .   Romain  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Romain","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French/Haitian Alain, Altagrace, Aurore, Camille, Dominique, Edele, Georges, Henri, Jacques, Jean-Marie, Jean-Michel, Jeanmarie.","French, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and English: variant of   Roman  ."]}]},{"name":"Leger","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Camille, Lucien, Pierre, Yvon, Antoine, Aurele, Emile, Jacques, Marcel, Zoel, Adelard.","French (<b>Léger</b>) and English: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Leudgari</i>, composed of the elements <i>leud</i> ‘people’ and <i>gari</i> (from <i>garwa</i>) ‘ready, eager’ or <i>gari</i> ‘spear’ and Latinized as <i>Leodegar(ius)</i>. The name was borne by a 7th-century Christian saint, bishop of Autun, whose fame contributed to the popularity of the name in France. See also   Ledger   and   St. Leger  .","French (<b>Léger</b>): nickname from <i>léger</i> ‘light, superficial’."],"variants":[{"name":"Lege","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alphie, Emile, Gaston, Henri, Leonce, Minus, Numa, Pierre, Rodolph.","German: topographic name meaning ‘swamp’.","Altered form of French <b>Léger</b> (see   Leger  )."]},{"name":"Legere","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Armand, Normand, Aurele, Jacques, Adelard, Alban, Antoine, Desire, Eloi, Monique, Yvon.","French (<b>Légère</b>): nickname from <i>légère</i>, a feminine form of <b>Léger</b> ‘light, superficial’ (see   Leger   2).","Altered form of French   Leger   1 or 2."]},{"name":"Lougee","meanings":["Channel Islands: altered form of <b>Laugee</b>, a variant of French <b>Lauger</b>, itself either a variant of <b>Léger</b> (see   Leger  ) or a variant, with fused definite article <i>l'</i>, of   Auger  .","History: The first recorded American bearer of this surname was John Lougee from the isle of Jersey. Born Jean Laugee and by trade a knitter, he was aged <i>c.</i> 18 or 19 when he emigrated to the USA in the late 1600s, settling in Exeter, NH, where he became known as John Lougee, marrying Anne, the daughter of Colonel Moses Gilman."]},{"name":"Ledger","meanings":["English: from a Norman personal name, <i>Leodegar</i>, Old French <i>Legier</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (see   Leger   1).","English: metonymic occupational name from Middle English <i>legger</i> ‘one who lays stone, a mason’, a derivative of Old English <i>lecgan</i> ‘to lay’.","Americanized form of French   Leger   1."]},{"name":"St. Leger","meanings":["French (<b>Saint-Léger</b>): habitational name from any of several places in various parts of France named Saint-Léger (from the dedication of their churches to Saint Leodegar, in French St. Léger, the martyred 7th-century bishop of Autun), or a nickname with the prefix <i>Saint</i> as an (ironic) attachment to the personal name or surname <i>Léger</i> (see   Leger   1).","Haitian (also <b>Saint-Léger</b>): from <i>Saint-Léger</i>, a nickname, ornamental name, or personal name composed of the French prefix <i>Saint</i> and the personal name <i>Léger</i> (see   Leger   1), or perhaps a habitational name from a place in Haiti called Saint-Léger (compare 1 above).","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Saint-Léger in La Manche or Saint-Léger-aux-Bois in Seine-Maritime, France (see 1 above)."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary St Leger was born in 1395, in Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom, her father, Thomas St. Leger, was 81 and her mother, Anne, was 82. She married Henry John Aucher II in 1435. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died on 28 October 1445, in Ashford, Kent, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 50, and was buried in Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1395–28 October 1445":"1395–28. oktoober 1445","1395–1445":"1395–1445","1398–1441":"1398–1441","1390–1485":"1390–1485","1415–1494":"1415–1494","1416–Male":"1416–Surnud","1314–Male":"1314–Surnud","1313–Female":"1313–Surnud","1395":"1395","1494":"1494","1390":"1390","Abt 1415":"umbes 1415","1415":"1415","1435":"1435","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1445":"1445","1398":"1398","1441":"1441","1485":"1485","1416":"1416","28 October 1445":"28. oktoober 1445","Ottringtown, Cambridge, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ashford, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Ashford, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Otterden, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Otterden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1395–28 October 1445":"1395–28. lokakuuta 1